cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically image demosaicing and denoising using deep learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with image processing. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses a generative adversarial network (GAN) for image reconstruction. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image reconstruction. Finally, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses perceptual optimization to ensure visual quality.
